chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Laws on abortion should start from shared aims: protect life and health, respect conscience in a pluralistic society, and ensure decisions are made safely and without needless delay. A workable framework keeps early pregnancy care private and medically accessible, sets clearly defined limits later in pregnancy tied to fetal viability or medical circumstances, and guarantees prompt exceptions for life-threatening or serious health conditions, rape or incest, and severe fetal anomalies—written plainly so clinicians can act without fear. Any legal approach should also invest heavily in prevention and support—accurate sex education, affordable contraception, prenatal and postpartum care, and practical resources for parenting, disability needs, and adoption—so fewer people face crisis pregnancies.
